description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit 2 Band 4 Senior Medical Secretaries within the Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Division of the Bristol Royal Hospital for Children:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Full Time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Part Time - 32 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced, enthusiastic and dedicated individuals to provide an effective and efficient secretarial service to the department. The post holders will have a range of secretarial/PA experience, ideally in a hospital environment, though other administration/PA experience will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in busy and sometimes demanding role, within supportive team, they must be good team players and enjoy working within a multidisciplinary team. The applicants should have good organisational and interpersonal skills and the ability to work well under pressure. As the post deals with patients, relatives and healthcare professionals on the phone, and occasionally face to face, applicants must have excellent communication skills and will be expected to have a courteous and efficient telephone manner. They need to have a good working knowledge of Microsoft Word, Excel, Outlook and Calendars.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from those who meet all of the essential criteria as set out in the person specification. This includes having a qualification in word processing or audio typist (or equivalent), educated to GCSE grade C or above (or equivalent) in English language and maths, and Business and Administration Level 3 NVQ or equivalent experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameElaine CordeyJob titleDeputy Medical Secretarial ManagerEmail addressElaine.Cordey@UHBW.nhs.ukTelephone number0117 34 27455Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Martin, Performance and Operations Manage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard.Martin@UHBW.NHS.UK&lt;/p&gt;
